1
00:00:01,751 --> 00:00:03,628
<i>Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.</i>

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>People who have used these drugs</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:10,719
<i>are now estimated</i>
<i>to total two million in Japan.</i>

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:14,347
<i>The number of people arrested</i>
<i>for drug-related offenses</i>

5
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:16,933
<i>is as many as 14,000 yearly.</i>

6
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:20,353
This is what you'll suggest to Kurosaki.

7
00:00:20,437 --> 00:00:21,813
"Let's get not just Nagata,

8
00:00:21,896 --> 00:00:25,191
but also the organization
that was selling drugs to him.

9
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:27,819
I'll go and investigate
their smuggling routes."

10
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:30,071
You think Kurosaki would fall for that?

11
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:31,865
You little shit.

12
00:00:32,532 --> 00:00:34,909
How about we go for an eyeball?

13
00:00:34,993 --> 00:00:35,827
Don't!

14
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:40,040
The Saeki Family that's been looking
after us needs some more manpower.

15
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:42,709
You.

16
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:45,253
Go help them for a few days.

17
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:46,296
Listen up.

18
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:49,799
One look at how they clean
and I can tell if they're useful.

19
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:52,469
If they seem trustworthy,
they'll get the goods.

20
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:54,220
Shouldn't be a bad deal.

21
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:55,638
Yes, sir.

22
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:57,724
-Right, Shinichi?
-I'm Shinji, sir.

23
00:00:57,807 --> 00:00:59,809
Does it fucking matter?

24
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,937
-I'm Shinichi--
-You too!

25
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:07,192
<i>If I infiltrate it, we can grasp</i>
<i>the entire flow of the cocaine.</i>

26
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:08,318
With this plan,

27
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:12,322
we can get more than just the people
who directly sold the cocaine to Nagata.

28
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:13,782
The client list.

29
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:16,743
Search for it. Find it. Bring it.
That's my condition.

30
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,455
Hello, sir!

31
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:25,919
Did you wipe all of this?

32
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:27,712
Sorry, it was me.

33
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:31,883
You pass.

34
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:32,801
What?

35
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:35,845
Go to the dock right now
and collect our monthly shipment.

36
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:37,055
What kind of shipment?

37
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:39,098
Cocaine.

38
00:01:39,849 --> 00:01:41,935
Someone else will handle the payment.

39
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:45,021
You just get the shipment
and contact me immediately.

40
00:01:45,104 --> 00:01:47,607
-Ask Shinichi the details.
-Yes, sir.

41
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:53,571
I just received the goods.

42
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:55,573
<i>Take them to the address I'm sending you.</i>

43
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:56,658
Yes, sir.

44
00:01:56,741 --> 00:01:58,618
SAEKI SEAFOOD COMPANY

45
00:01:58,701 --> 00:01:59,744
You still a newbie?

46
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:00,787
Just be quick.

47
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:03,581
I always get it done on time.

48
00:02:09,587 --> 00:02:11,131
Hey, you're in the way. Move.

49
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:12,215
Sorry.

50
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:49,085
Come to Parking Lot #5
in the Bay Area right now.

51
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:51,296
I found the Saeki Family's cocaine route.

52
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,799
Did the NCD find it that quick?

53
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:57,677
No, I found it on my own.

54
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:01,014
They already trust you that much?

55
00:03:01,097 --> 00:03:02,724
<i>They smuggle it from overseas,</i>

56
00:03:02,807 --> 00:03:05,643
collect it on fishing boats,
and hide it in the fish.

57
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:07,979
They deliver those to fishmongers,

58
00:03:08,062 --> 00:03:10,607
and take the cocaine
to apartments they've rented.

59
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:11,858
Got it.

60
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:13,568
Where are the goods?

61
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:14,777
I have them.

62
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,031
Even if we don't leak
more info to the NCD,

63
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:19,991
this should be enough as evidence.

64
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,035
That's true.

65
00:03:22,118 --> 00:03:24,829
Come before the Saeki guys get suspicious.

66
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,581
I'll hide nearby with the coke.

67
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,958
All right. I'll arrange it immediately.

68
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:31,377
That's mission accomplished, right?

69
00:03:35,381 --> 00:03:37,008
Great job.

70
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,860
What are you up to?

71
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:57,463
SAEKI SEAFOOD COMPANY

72
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:05,805
Did ya really think
cleaning would earn you trust?

73
00:05:05,888 --> 00:05:09,475
I thought you were suspicious
as hell right from the start.

74
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:17,191
Who ordered you to steal our goods?

75
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:19,694
I told you.

76
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:21,654
That's not it.

77
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:23,740
What else would it be?!

78
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:25,825
What are you and Matsubara scheming?

79
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,327
Matsubara?

80
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:29,162
Hey, bring him in.

81
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:30,371
Sir.

82
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:32,498
Aren't you a dealer for Matsubara?

83
00:05:33,249 --> 00:05:34,667
-Yes.
-Come here, you.

84
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:35,835
Get in there.

85
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:38,504
Get a move on!

86
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:39,756
Mr. Matsubara!

87
00:05:43,801 --> 00:05:45,470
Umezawa.

88
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:49,140
What the hell did you do?

89
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,892
No, I didn't--

90
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:53,478
Hey! Drop the cheap act!

91
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:57,023
You two tried to steal
our goods, didn't you?

92
00:05:58,316 --> 00:05:59,192
No.

93
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:01,778
It wasn't me.

94
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:04,113
He did it all on his own.

95
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:12,497
You think a punk like this has the balls
to steal from the yakuza on his own?

96
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:15,541
And you're not much
better than him yourself.

97
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:21,089
Whose orders are you two following?

98
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:22,507
Spit it out already.

99
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,846
I swear…

100
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:33,309
I didn't know about this.

101
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:47,448
Umezawa!

102
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,326
Say something, you fucker!

103
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:53,412
Umezawa!

104
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,331
I have nothing to do with this!

105
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:57,834
-You bastard. Why?
-Hey.

106
00:06:57,917 --> 00:07:01,045
-Why are you making me go through…
-Hey!

107
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:05,800
Why are you pissing in my office?

108
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:08,010
You're getting the floor all filthy!

109
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:15,435
I'm telling you
not to stain the damn floor!

110
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,361
Hey, Shinji.

111
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:26,362
I'm Shinichi.

112
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,989
Who the fuck cares!

113
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:29,991
Wipe the floor thoroughly later.

114
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:33,035
It gets tough to clean
when the blood starts to harden.

115
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,078
Yes, sir.

116
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:39,917
Let's move on, then.

117
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:43,629
Your turn next.

118
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:48,676
Please forgive me!

119
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,761
For what?

120
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,930
What would I forgive you for?

121
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:55,641
You must feel guilty
if you're asking for forgiveness.

122
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:58,478
What do you want forgiveness for?

123
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:01,689
I mean, this is a misunderstanding.

124
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,442
What misunderstanding?

125
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:06,819
I'm asking you why you stopped the car

126
00:08:06,903 --> 00:08:09,822
and checked the cargo
while transporting the goods.

127
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:11,699
Because…

128
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:17,330
I got worried whether the goods
were still there or got stolen.

129
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:18,372
The heck?

130
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:21,375
How would anyone steal them
from a moving vehicle?

131
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:23,461
Why would you suddenly worry about that?

132
00:08:23,544 --> 00:08:27,423
And what did you do after stopping
the car and taking out the fish, huh?

133
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,883
Answer, damn it!

134
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:34,889
I'm the type to get worried
if I don't double-check things!

135
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:39,894
Like whether I turned the lights off
or locked my door when I go out.

136
00:08:39,977 --> 00:08:42,522
I would even go back home
to check sometimes.

137
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:44,815
Don't you ever do that?

138
00:08:47,818 --> 00:08:49,111
All the time.

139
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,532
Did you think that dumb excuse would work?

140
00:08:54,742 --> 00:08:57,495
Only two more centimeters to your heart.

141
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:58,704
Strange, isn't it?

142
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:03,626
You're talking just fine right now,
but if I come any closer, you're dead.

143
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:07,380
How about it? Want to try dying once?

144
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:13,386
Is this the place?

145
00:09:13,469 --> 00:09:15,179
Who the hell are you?

146
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:19,100
Freeze!

147
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:21,852
Freeze!

148
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:23,896
Who are you?

149
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:27,483
I'm with the NCD.
I'll shoot if you resist.

150
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:33,781
You're bluffing.

151
00:09:33,864 --> 00:09:36,492
I'm not. I repeat.
I'll shoot if you resist.

152
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:37,702
Get on the ground.

153
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:39,495
Man up, Shinichi. Go.

154
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:40,538
Yes, sir.

155
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:50,298
I'm dead serious.

156
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:53,884
Shit.

157
00:09:57,054 --> 00:09:58,097
How did you find me?

158
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,515
GPS tracker.

159
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:04,562
Take this.

160
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:07,356
What's this, all of a sudden?

161
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,691
A good luck charm.

162
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:11,611
What gives? You're creeping me out.

163
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:14,822
You'll have to protect yourself.

164
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:16,532
You weren't trying to be nice?

165
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:18,993
The charm?

166
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:21,954
Yeah, it's not like
I trusted you completely.

167
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:25,541
The whole time?

168
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,376
Yeah.

169
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,296
NAKANO EAST AVENUE

170
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,051
SAEKI SEAFOOD COMPANY

171
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:35,968
<i>Wait a second.</i>

172
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:37,970
There were guards outside.

173
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:40,389
They won't be moving for a while.

174
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:49,065
-What do you want?
-Stop right there.

175
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:50,066
-Move.
-Fuck you!

176
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:28,020
Damn it.

177
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:32,108
Couldn't you have saved me sooner?

178
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:33,859
I thought I was going to die!

179
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:36,779
I told you,
you would have to protect yourself.

180
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:38,823
Come on…

181
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:41,283
I'll say it again.

182
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:43,619
Get on the ground.

183
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:45,955
Watch out!

184
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:56,382
Don't let your guard down
in a yakuza office.

185
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:11,397
How can you still move?

186
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:14,233
This isn't enough to put me down!

187
00:12:14,316 --> 00:12:15,317
I knew it.

188
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:18,154
You were doing speed, weren't you?

189
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:20,030
Taking from the goods?

190
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,615
Damn junkie zombie.

191
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:22,783
Get him!

192
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:32,918
Don't move!

193
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:34,712
Or he dies.

194
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:50,603
Fucking bastard.

195
00:12:58,527 --> 00:12:59,695
Kurosaki.

196
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,622
What do we do with him?

197
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:12,208
Good question.

198
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:15,794
We can't just let him go like this.

199
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,464
Guess we have to kill him.

200
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:21,342
But killing a narcotics agent…

201
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:23,302
What other choice is there?

202
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:24,345
Okay, sir.

203
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:26,055
Is the other guy taken care of?

204
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:27,097
Yes.

205
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,474
Shinji went to do it.

206
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:40,736
We're back.

207
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:45,991
We checked with the police,
and the body is confirmed to be Nagata's.

208
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:50,329
I won't tell a soul
that I bought from the Saeki Family!

209
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:53,040
Please, have mercy on me!

210
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,044
Any word from Kurosaki?

211
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:58,712
Nothing yet.

212
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:04,134
What is he doing, all while
ignoring calls from his superior?

213
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,304
He hasn't read our messages either.

214
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:08,472
What should we do?

215
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:11,350
If an agent stops making
their scheduled check-ins,

216
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:13,602
we're supposed to report it
to our higher-ups,

217
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:16,272
considering the chance
they might have been attacked.

218
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:18,857
We would do so for anyone other than him,

219
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:22,236
but in his case,
he's probably just ignoring the rules.

220
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:24,363
No doubt about it.

221
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:28,659
Damn it, will he ever stop
acting like a loose cannon?

222
00:14:30,911 --> 00:14:32,037
Could it be

223
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:35,541
that he went back to the hospital
to continue questioning Kaga?

224
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:37,835
He does tend to be stubborn.

225
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:45,843
Let's move.

226
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:00,900
Oh, sorry.

227
00:15:14,663 --> 00:15:15,998
Oh, sorry.

228
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:19,877
-The doctor just now. Inaba, find him.
-Yes, sir.

229
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,170
Aoshima, call a nurse.

230
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:22,212
-Okay!
-The nurse call?

231
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,840
-It's right there.
-Okay.

232
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:26,550
How many will die?

233
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:29,011
What the heck is he up to?

234
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:42,733
Help me with this.

235
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,610
I'm coming.

236
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:46,570
Shinji.

237
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:49,281
You got Kaga, right?

238
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:50,908
Yeah.

239
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:53,327
We can't turn back anymore.

240
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:55,079
What's going to happen to us?

241
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:57,164
Calm down, would you?

242
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:01,043
The boss made the call,
so we've got no choice.

243
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:05,798
But I can't… murder someone.

244
00:16:05,881 --> 00:16:08,300
You just came back from killing one!

245
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:11,387
But all I did was put drugs in his IV bag!

246
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,973
-That's no different!
-It is.

247
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:17,851
Killing someone directly is way worse
than killing them with drugs!

248
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:21,605
It's still murder in the end.

249
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:25,067
Seriously?

250
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:27,569
Now, come on.

251
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:29,989
Do as the boss said.

252
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:33,200
Beat him to death with these bats.

253
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:34,118
No!

254
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:35,119
I don't want to!

255
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,913
Drug them, club them,
what's the difference?

256
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:41,250
Well, you would rather kill
a cockroach with insect spray

257
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:43,002
than squash one, right?

258
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:45,129
At least we can't see his face!

259
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:46,046
Now, do it!

260
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:49,341
You do it first.

261
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,135
You're the elder brother.

262
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:52,803
Then you have to do what I say.

263
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:54,221
Now, do it.

264
00:16:54,304 --> 00:16:55,431
I don't want to!

265
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:57,224
You do it first, please.

266
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:00,853
All right.

267
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:03,647
Watch me do it.

268
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:10,696
Take this!

269
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,034
You do it too.

270
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:22,666
Fuck!

271
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:26,003
Hey, go for the head. Hit the damn head.

272
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:28,547
You went for the stomach too!

273
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:34,470
If we don't do it,
the boss will do it to us.

274
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,114
Really now?

275
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:57,993
What's a section chief
doing out in the field?

276
00:17:58,827 --> 00:18:00,788
I came to collect Kaga's corpse.

277
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:02,623
We're not done with it yet.

278
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:04,875
As I'm sure you're well aware,

279
00:18:05,709 --> 00:18:08,253
we get jurisdiction once a suspect dies.

280
00:18:11,715 --> 00:18:14,134
One of ours was aiming for Kaga.

281
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:17,262
Quite the competent officer, at that.

282
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:20,516
Stay out of our way, will you?

283
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:22,768
You're the one getting in our way!

284
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:27,648
I hear Kurosaki
jumped off the roof with Kaga.

285
00:18:30,859 --> 00:18:32,277
If you come any closer,

286
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,530
I'll jump off!

287
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,991
-He's so high he might actually do it.
-Do it.

288
00:18:38,075 --> 00:18:39,827
I'm not bluffing!

289
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:53,215
We could arrest Kurosaki
for attempted murder.

290
00:18:53,298 --> 00:18:54,758
Don't be ridiculous!

291
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,802
He risked his life to bring Kaga in!

292
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,971
You don't get to make that call.

293
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,348
The police do.

294
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:21,577
Quite the surprise, honestly.

295
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:26,248
I was almost certain you were just
planning to leech off of our business.

296
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:29,042
But then a narcotics agent shows up.

297
00:19:30,085 --> 00:19:31,712
So who exactly are you?

298
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:33,714
Another NCD agent?

299
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:37,259
Or just a dog supplying info to that man?

300
00:19:37,342 --> 00:19:38,427
Which is it?

301
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:53,817
Complete silence again?
I'm bored of that already.

302
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:56,945
Okay, so I'm not going to get
anything out of you, yeah?

303
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:57,988
All right.

304
00:19:58,071 --> 00:19:59,781
-I'll just kill you, then--
-Wait!

305
00:20:01,825 --> 00:20:03,076
It's like you said.

306
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:05,162
I'm an agent with the NCD.

307
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,623
I went undercover to investigate.

308
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:08,707
Got it.

309
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:10,792
-Time to kill you!
-But why?

310
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:13,712
If you kill an agent,
you'll get in deep shit.

311
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:15,505
We already killed one.

312
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:17,674
Killing one is one thing, but two?

313
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:19,801
The NCD will never leave you alone.

314
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:23,013
Is killing two really that different
from killing one?

315
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:25,182
If I let you live,
they'll find out anyway.

316
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:28,227
If you let me live,
I won't tell anyone what I saw here.

317
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:30,771
-Such an obvious lie.
-It's not a damn lie!

318
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:32,397
Watch your damn mouth!

319
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,274
Sorry. It's not a lie.

320
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:35,442
Too late. You're dead.

321
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:37,152
In that case!

322
00:20:39,196 --> 00:20:40,781
How about we team up?

323
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:41,823
What?

324
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:45,035
Your group killed an agent, right?

325
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:47,246
They'll find this place eventually.

326
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:50,457
I'll just have some youngster
take the fall for it.

327
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:52,376
It's the murder of an agent!

328
00:20:52,459 --> 00:20:53,877
It won't end with that.

329
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:56,213
They'll do a thorough search.

330
00:20:57,297 --> 00:21:02,135
You'll have to halt business,
and worst case, you might get caught too.

331
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:05,138
And what can you do about it?

332
00:21:05,222 --> 00:21:07,182
I can prevent that from happening.

333
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:08,850
As if you could.

334
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,060
I can!

335
00:21:11,144 --> 00:21:12,396
That's not all.

336
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:16,191
From now on,
I'll leak the NCD's intel to you.

337
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:20,529
Would you please let me be an S for you?

338
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:22,739
What's an S?

339
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:24,783
A spy.

340
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:30,330
If we do that, you'll never get caught
and can make big money.

341
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:33,542
How about it? I think it's a good deal.

342
00:21:34,835 --> 00:21:35,794
Got any proof?

343
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:37,379
What?

344
00:21:37,462 --> 00:21:39,214
Proof that you're with the NCD.

345
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,717
That's…

346
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,094
Show me some ID
if you're really with them.

347
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:46,847
I don't have it now.

348
00:21:46,930 --> 00:21:47,806
Why not?

349
00:21:48,557 --> 00:21:51,101
I can't carry it with me
while I'm undercover.

350
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:52,686
All right.

351
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:54,021
Your phone, then.

352
00:21:55,522 --> 00:21:57,316
If you're really with the NCD,

353
00:21:57,399 --> 00:22:00,235
you'll have mutual coworkers
with the other NCD guy.

354
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:03,864
If their numbers
are in both of your phones,

355
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,407
I'll trust you.

356
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:08,952
However, if they aren't…

357
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:12,331
it's over for you.

358
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:22,799
If we fill the corpse with holes
and throw it in the sea,

359
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:25,844
conger eels will swim inside it

360
00:22:26,636 --> 00:22:28,555
and swiftly turn it into bones.

361
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:33,977
And then,
it will never rise to the surface again.

362
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:38,273
It will be over with this.

363
00:22:41,068 --> 00:22:42,527
Right.

364
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,279
He's dead.

365
00:23:26,363 --> 00:23:29,241
Being a dealer for him was part
of your undercover investigation?

366
00:23:29,324 --> 00:23:30,158
Yes.

367
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:32,702
Please let me be your S!

368
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:35,288
<i>It's the police that protect</i>
<i>this country from threats.</i>

369
00:23:35,372 --> 00:23:37,207
-Don't forget that.
-Yes, sir.

370
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,584
<i>This case belongs to the police.</i>

371
00:23:39,668 --> 00:23:41,378
Fuck that!

372
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:44,464
<i>What do you take people's lives for?</i>

373
00:23:45,132 --> 00:23:50,011
While you were trying to rack up points,
we were about to get killed!

374
00:23:50,804 --> 00:23:52,430
<i>Results mean everything.</i>

375
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:55,016
I don't care about the life
of a punk like you.

376
00:23:55,100 --> 00:24:01,022
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

377
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:02,065
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan
